    <item>
      <title>CHAoOS: Korok Blights</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/524944</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">f9da7548a6320bbb0c041bda55a2ef1ab0dd3ea8</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2024 21:51:54 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6681d31161317.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6681d322c93a0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6681d32514cc2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6681d32521534.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i class="SelectedElement"&gt;Hahaha... Now THIS is a janky mod! (This is more of a demonstration of what is possible rather than an actually good mod)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Basically, all &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;"korok seed" koroks can spawn one of the four Blights!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Of course,&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; this mod prevents you from obtaining korok seeds while it is installed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Again, this mod can be VERY janky. Sometimes it spawns the blights under the ground, sometimes it lags the game for a little bit. Sometimes it will keep spawning blights continuously (which eventually crashed the game)! Also, none of the blights can truly be killed because I did not want to re-write their ai (this of course means that they can not "drop" items too).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;i&gt;“What is CHAoOS???”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;CHAoOS is the “Clearly Horrible Arrangement of Opponents Series.” It is not meant to be balanced or polished, but those things are not unwelcome. The goal of this series is to provide interesting fighting experiences –even if they are a bit chaotic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;Modder notes:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;---This mod was made with three actors (although it probably could have been made with just two actors). Basically, there are two types of "korok seed" koroks:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Npc_HiddenKorokGround&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Npc_HiddenKorokFly&lt;/span&gt;. I changed the actors that use those names to something that I call a "cluster npc." The cluster npc "holds" a shield with 0hp that randomly drops one of the four blights.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;From what I can tell, the reason that some koroks spawn blights continuously is because the cluster npc that spawns/holds the 0hp shield continuously spawns and despawns --therefore continously spawning the 0hp shield and THEREFORE continuously dropping a new blight. In the video, I believe that the cluster npc is falling in the water and despawning, and then respawning again.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Enjoy~ (if that's even possible lol)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/chaooskorokblights.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <category>Enemy</category>
      <category>Enemy</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Corruption's Curse</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/523990</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">fcc3e3dfae989f62be581bc68b7393b6deaaeaf7</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2024 16:43:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667fbe1b5a5eb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667ba74acc700.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667ba74ae02eb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667ba74b0739c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667ba74be273c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/667ba74c6d12e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Update rules.txt&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Added line in rules.txt "version = 3"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Added a line in rules.txt&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;This mod is called Corruption's Curse.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod aims to add a new variant of enemies and will also be adding a couple extra features to improve gameplay. It adds a new Lynel know as the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;corrupted variant&lt;/span&gt;, a fun challenge for the player will still having amazing combat power. The mod also adds the new enemy variant for a bunch of enemies, as well as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;new paraglider&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;faster speeds&lt;/span&gt;. The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;stal enemies&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;have been retextured&amp;nbsp;and with an upgrade in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;speed&lt;/span&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;power&lt;/span&gt;, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;strength&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;nbsp; All major bosses are revamped such as the blights&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;divine beasts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the blights at &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Hyrule Castle&lt;/span&gt;, and the main boss&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;ganon&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;himself. A bunch of weapons have been buffed mainly all the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;legendary weapons&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;The mod is pretty self explanatory, but here are the new or unreleased features and content&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;New Content:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Lynel&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New weapons&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New enemy Variant *&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Partially&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&amp;nbsp;in beta&lt;/span&gt;*&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New title screen logo&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New title screen background&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Legendary Weapons' Buffed *&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unreleased&lt;/span&gt;*&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stal enemy revamp&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Lynel has been customized to have a great experience while also being a nice and fun challenge.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;The Lynel's stats:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Damage Output: 2000&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Health: 16340&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Speed 1.2 faster&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;The New enemies are released but some are unreleased due to delays.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Enemy Variants:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Moblin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Lizalfoes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Bokoblins&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Chu Chu&amp;nbsp;-&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unreleased&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Hinox&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Octorock&amp;nbsp;-&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unreleased&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;New Stal enemies Variants for all enemy types*&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;hr&gt;The New weapons are Not released due to actors failing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;New Weapons:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul class="SelectedElement"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Ancient Bladesaw&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Unreleased in beta*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Ancient Short Sword&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Released in beta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Ancient Bow&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Unreleased in beta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Ancient Gear&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Unreleased in beta*&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Ancient Spear&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Unreleased in beta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Soul Dagger&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*Unreleased in beta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Lance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted sword&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Corrupted Shield&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Blood Stals addition:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bokoblin- blood type&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Moblin- blood type&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lizalfos- blood type&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Stalnox- blood type&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;I really hope you enjoy this mod, because I'm really excited to work on it. I know a lot of it is unfinished but that was due to time restraint, I have things in my life as well school, family, etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Again, thank you so much I plan to release an update eventually.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Credits and Special thanks to:&lt;/h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;ShadowMarth! - permission was given to use some pieces of his actors(TY shadowmarth)&lt;br&gt;Special Thanks to: The calamity refuge discord!&lt;br&gt;Special Thanks to: Nebroc!&lt;br&gt;Special Thanks to: Wine!&lt;br&gt;Special Thanks to: Charlie&lt;br&gt;This mod is dedicated to: Bella:)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;VERY IMPORTANT PLEASE READ OR MOD MAY NOT WORK&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;Playing as a standalone, ROTP, Second Wind, or DAR&lt;br&gt;-Download the zip&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;-Add the mod to bcml and click install&lt;br&gt;-click show handles and grab the mod&lt;br&gt;-now reorder the mod list and put the mod at the very top&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;IT MUST BE AT THE TOP OR IT WILL CAUSE PROBLEMS!!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;hr&gt;IF YOU PLAN TO UPLOAD THIS ON YT, TWITCH, OR ANY OTHER SERVICE I EXPECT CREDITS TO SKYSAURE AND BLACKJAY07, AS WELL AS LINKS PLEASE, Thank you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;LOCATION:&lt;/h2&gt;The location of the challenge is in the:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Nautelle Wetlands&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Kind of by the south lomei labyrinth look on the map)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/corruptions_curse_-_beta_109-1.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Mod Packs</category>
      <category>Mod Packs</category>
    </item>
