    <item>
      <title>Breath of The Wild: New Journey</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/520359</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">eef20d68387b5c19b5bef5875c287811f2d3f0a7</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2024 16:02:22 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/666b18083c13e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/666b180974f94.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hi everyone!&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And with great pleasure I announce the mod I've been working on for a month: New Journey.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is not a simple botw mod, but it is a small miniature Zelda, a kind of fan game that uses the botw engine. (obviously it's not a fangame because it can't work without different rules)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;But let's get to the point. What do you have to do in this mod?&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will have to find the 40 triforce fragments hidden in the dungeons. The 40 fragments are actually the orbs, I couldn't change the icon.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;the dungeons are not shrines, but are structures that I created, while some areas have been completely redesigned. The game loses its open-world nature in this mod and approaches a type of gameplay similar to SM64.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Needless to say, the original Botw is unplayable with this mod installed, so uninstall it when you're done.&amp;nbsp;(it is best to have only this mod installed when you play it)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;INSTALLATION GUIDE:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Once you extract the zip file, you will find a bnp file. use BCML to install it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You will find another folder called StartSavefile.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Contains the save file with which to start a new game.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;THIS IS NOT OPTIONAL.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The save file is vital to the mod's functioning, so make a backup of your current save file:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;..\Cemu_2.0-77\mlc01\usr\save\00050000\101c9500\user\80000001&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;the 80000001 folder is the one that&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;contains the save file with your data, remember to copy it somewhere before replacing it with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;folder with the same name you find in StartSaveData or you lost your data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Due to various problems during the development of this mod, you may have errors in the item texts, which are not shown.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you don't see some texts, I advise you to set the language to Italian. Everything should work there.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;don't worry, everything that is part of the mod is in English anyway.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;you can skip the rest, the npcs work as usual since I couldn't change the dialogues.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;remember to follow the simple rules:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;These simple rules are used to fully enjoy the mod, since I can't reprogram the game or make it too heavy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1) Do not go beyond the limits of the areas&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;: Each area has very high walls (mountains). obviously they are climbable but you won't find anything beyond them so don't climb over them. (they are very tall, you recognize them)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2) Don't move the Travel Medallion:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since the game moves with teleports, the Travel Medallion is used to return to the main city.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3) Move only with teleports:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The areas are all closed and separated from each other, use teleports to reach them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4)ALWAYS TAKE THE HEARTCONTAINER FROM THE GODDESS!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;this is important. if you play in Italian, the heart container is the first choice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;since there are 40 precise Orbs in the game, if you choose the stamina container you can no longer get the master sword. so be careful.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Don't worry. you will find stamina containers anyway&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;OPTIONAL RULES:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;use graphics packages to set the day at 12:00 (day) Avoid some light glitches&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;remove random spawning of Lizalfos (they can ruin the game progression because sometimes have unbreakable sword)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thats All.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Follow the installation instructions carefully!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I think I've told you everything.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/breathofthewild_newjourney.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Maps</category>
      <category>Maps</category>
    </item>
