    <item>
      <title>Girly Animation Pack</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/49763</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">98fc7bd1a927bd725707fc405ee93a6d28e64c8d</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2024 22:32:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/657dbb71aa2a1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/657dbba3bc638.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/65b2e449ac4fd.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/5fe12aa2906b4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/5fe12aa699fbc.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/5fe914ba339ef.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/5fe12ab3298ee.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6011fc5d267ef.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/603adb96e36da.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/603adf6e9a1d6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61a9461f0dff9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/61a9461ecbe64.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6218100147823.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/62181000eb62e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/62181000f1e9c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/62181016862bd.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Version 10.7&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;On this update:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;Fixed on section 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;, using the "&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="OrangeColor"&gt;Girly Running&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;" option (the first one), the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;dashing run animation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;, that made no steps sound at all (really weird!).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;Deleted on section 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;, the "&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="OrangeColor"&gt;Classic Girly Running&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;" option (it was added in version 10.6): after several tests, it's not longer necessary and the "&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;Girly Running&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;" option is working as expected no matter the number of fps you're playing the game.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;Remade on section 15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;, on the "&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="OrangeColor"&gt;Girly Default Glider&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;" option (the first one), the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;opening paraglider animation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;, as the one included in version 10.6 displayed a lot of trembling even using 30fps. Frankly speaking, this animation is cursed. The new one looks better but is not perfect, so I'm giving up on doing more changes to it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;Small change on section Extra 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt; (game &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="OrangeColor"&gt;logo replacements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;): the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;gray part of the logo when loading&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt; a savegame (the one being replaced slowly in white --or red-- while loading) is now almost as brighter as the default one (on version 10.6 was so dark, it was almost invisible).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_00.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_index_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Info &amp;amp; Acknowledgments&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Installing the Mod&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Description of every option&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Troubleshooting&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Other Mods&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_info_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod brings a big overhaul over Link’s more common animations: idles, walk, run, talk… a hundred of animations have been replaced in order to give to a female player, a more girly appearance, as seen in most of the female NPC in the game.&amp;nbsp;Several styles for each replacement are available to mix and get an almost unique style for your gameplay. But in fact, now you can&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;reverse it&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;and apply&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;default Link animations&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;(so, for example, you can bring back your beloved&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;tomboy&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;Linkle in Linkle 3!).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ko-Fi:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://ko-fi.com/i2mods" target="_blank"&gt;https://ko-fi.com/i2mods&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support my works by buying me a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a href="https://ko-fi.com/i2mods" target="_blank"&gt;coffee&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;:)&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;None of this would have been possible without the invaluable help of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1681976"&gt;Amiibolad&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(one of the key authors of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/179455"&gt;Zelda's Ballad mod&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;who kindly shared his knowledge on how to use NPC animations on the player), the collaboration of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1739516"&gt;Sockpoppet&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;(who hand-picked some of the animations and tested a lot of beta versions) and many, many people who shared their feedback in the comments section, helping me to find problems and fix issues during all this time. Also, without&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/skins/163132"&gt;Linkle mod&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;I would never have learned how to mod the game, so it was the thing responsible to put everything in motion.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_install_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;Don't use the 1-click install option!&lt;br&gt;Please do this Instead:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you are upgrading or reinstalling the mod, uninstall it first.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Download the BNP in a folder&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;install it on BCML&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;During the setup, a window with options will appear:&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Ensure you check&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;one option on each section&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Suggested ones are marked with an asterisk.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Install if&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;AFTER&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;your replacement mod (Linkle, Zelda…).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/games/6386"&gt;Nintendo Switch&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;users:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Please visit the port page &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/505453"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; (thanks to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/3290467" data-id="member_3290467"&gt;Zeus-Dev&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/168244"&gt;Zelda's Ballad&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;users:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Please, ensure you have installed Zelda's Ballad&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;without custom animations&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/168235"&gt;Linkle 2&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;mod users:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Girly Animation Pack will just work, nothing else is needed.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/406768"&gt;Linkle 3&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;mod users:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;I would suggest to also install the&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/441448"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patcher&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;after&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;the Girly Animation Pack, to fix&amp;nbsp;Linkle 3.0.1&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;too long arms&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;(especially noticeable after installing the Girly Animation Pack) and also to be able to install Linkle 2 armor mods in Linkle 3. For convenience, a&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Lite&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;version of this patch has been included in the Girly Animation Pack as an extra option during the installation (you can install one or another or even both, as the full one will upgrade the Lite).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;u&gt;DISCLAIMER&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Resources from Linkle 3 mod are used with authorization. Although it's not mandatory, to keep copyright things in order if you select Linkle 3 options you should have installed too Linkle 3 mod.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;Other&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;player replacements users:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Girly Animation Pack should work, unless they have custom animations.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Tip:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Once installed, in BCML you can press at any time the EXPLORE button and, in that folder, you will see the choices you made during the installation (in case you want to reinstall the mod with different options, upgrade it to a new version, etc).&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Disclaimer:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;I'm not related to any player modding team&lt;/u&gt;, my work is independent&amp;nbsp;and I try to solve bugs and improve as much as I can on my scarce free time. This is all for fun, for me, for you, for everyone!&amp;nbsp;And as long as you enjoy it, just keep playing. Thanks you so much!&lt;/i&gt;&amp;nbsp;:)&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_description_c.png"&gt;&lt;br&gt;This section explains each option in the Options Window you see during the installation:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Standing idle&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_01a.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Girly standing *&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Your hero will wait in a cute girly style, as seen in most of the female NPC in the game.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_1b.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3 standing&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Your hero will wait as seen in the Linkle 3 mod.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap1def.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Link standing&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Link animation will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;After a half a minute or so, &lt;u&gt;random idles will play&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;see Section 16&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;2. Random idles while standing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_relax_r.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_sleep_r2.apng"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_shy_r.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Girly casual *&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Will use these idles instead of the default ones:&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Cute Relax (first picture): Played during the day or the night.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Sleepy Head (second one): Played only during the night.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Embarrassed (third): Played only if not wearing any shirt.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Link actions&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Default Link random idles will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;3. Walking style&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_02a.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Girly walk *&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will walk in a cute girly style, as seen in most of the female NPC in the game.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_02b.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Positive walk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will walk in a girly, somehow in a livelier style, as seen in some female NPC.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_02c.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;onfident walk&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will walk in a girly, more confident style as seen in a certain queen in the game.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_2d.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3 walk&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will walk in a feminine fashion as seen in Linkle 3 mod. Install along Linkle 3 running style is recommended.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap2def.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Link walk&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Link animation will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;4. How to stop walking&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_03a_r.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Cute extra step *&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Your hero will end walking with an extra, short graceful, small step; meaning she will still move a little when you release the controller stick (that could be dangerous in some places…).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Just stop&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will stop walking as soon as you release the controller stick.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_03c_r.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3 stop&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Your hero will stop walking as seen on Linkle 3 mod.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Default Link stop:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Link animation will be used.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;5. Running style&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/gap_04a.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Girly running *&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Your hero will run in a cute girly style as seen in most of the female NPC in the g